<TITLE> NBR, RAB raid 5 showrooms of Venus Jewellers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NBR, RAB raid 5 showrooms of Venus Jewellers Dhaka, Aug 7 (bdnews24.com) - Officials of the National Board of Revenue, RAB and intelligence agencies made simultaneous raids on five show rooms of Venus Jewellers in the city, and the house of its owner, on suspicion of VAT and income tax evasion. The owner of the company, Gangacharan Malakar, is presently in India, family members and employees told the officials. RAB-3 Squadron leader Khalid Shams of told bdnews24.com: "The raids started at 3.30pm Thursday." They continued till 10pm at night. "The NBR officials are in charge of the raids. Officials of RAB and intelligence agency NSI are assisting them." Six separate teams of NBR, RAB and NSI made simultaneous raids on the jeweller's showrooms at Eastern Plaza, Basundhara City, Gulshan Navana Tower, Baitul Mokarram and Gangacharan Malakar's Wari residence, he said. NBR second secretary Zakir Hossain was at Eastern Plaza. He said evidence of evading VAT of at least Tk 27 lakh had been found in the Eastern Plaza showroom alone. RAB-3 officer Zarrar Hossain estimated from what they had seen so far, the jewellers paid tax on only one third of the ornaments they sold, perhaps even less. Officials said the total amount of VAT and income tax withheld by Venus Jewellers may amount to several crore taka. bdnews24.c
